"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> was founded in 1974 to voice concern about declining standards in society, particularly in relation to their effect on children and families.  Supporters meet bi-monthly and those attending our last meeting include a retired secondary school head teacher,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> a minister of religion, retired nursing professionals, parents and a local councillor.  We are of varying ages. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We recognise and applaud much of what the BBC has continued to offer ever since its beginnings.  There is much which earns public </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">appreciation.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The BBC Trust is an important body and we appreciate it because of the BBC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">'s persistence in pushing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> back the frontiers of acceptability.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It has always been argued</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> it is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> perverse not to acknowledge</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> today</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that watching sexual promisc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">uity and indulging in the portrayal of extreme violence contribute to the emergence of a violent society.  Numerous competent research projects have judged this to be so.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It was our view</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, expressed in the 1970's and 1980's to the then British Board of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Film Censors, that the industry's rather than the public's choice influenced the Board's decision</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and standards.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">So also with the BBC.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  Reconsideration of the BBC Trust's role offers an opportunity to consider Lord Reith's original vision and aim to real</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ise it more completely than at present.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Prime Minister h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> acknowledged that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Great Britain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is a Christian country.  History describes plenty of shortcomings but today international scholars such as Dr </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Vishal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Mangalwadi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in his mammoth research </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">The Book that made your world - How the Bible created the soul of Western civilisation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, challenge</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Western nations to take their spiritual and moral foundations much more seriously as serious signs of decay threaten.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We would like to make the following</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> recommendations:-</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Trust is a watchdog.  It should be independent of the BBC and separate from it.  Financial independency is important.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  Its power should be increased and it should be able to forbid repeat performances of outrageous programmes.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Pro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gramme makers should seek to express and be participant in the humble daily life, pursuits, interests and concerns of the nation as a whole, facing as it does the challenges of the modern age, the influence (not always positive) of immigrants from other cu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ltures and the important influences of visual imagery to a young generation increasingly experiencing freedom of choice through </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he continuous development of technology.  The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">iPlayer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is a new hazard for the young.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The country </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Europe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> as a whole</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> pays </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">scrupulous attention to what people </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are sold</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to eat but continues to be unwilling for adequate bounds to be set on what a publicly financed service is to provide as suitable to be watched by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">all and especially by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the vulnerable.  Permissiveness is the outc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ome - with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">increasing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">social and personal consequences which can be tragic.  The BBC should not be afraid even of criticism in shutting the door - belatedly - on what is becoming more and more extreme.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">"Ordinary people" - the general public - </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">li</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ve individual, important, exacting personal lives.  They cannot be expected to take part </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">adequately </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in the present complicated complaints process.  If the BBC is to demonstrate real concern for the public good it should devise a system more </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">suitable than t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he one offered</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to achieve a real, widespread public expression of views.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  Failure to act on the public's contributions and criticisms in the past when complaints have been made does not encourage.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The ordinary lives of ordinary people are actually often a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">bsorbingly interesting when the broadcaster's art is at its best.  There could be a broader range of programmes of wholesomeness.  These need not be dull.  People get bored with violence and crime.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Some trailers just before the 10 o'clock news on BBC1 are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> appallingly violent.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Bad language is usually regarded as a sign of intellectual lack.  Why </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">should audiences</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> be exposed to what most people would not tolerate, let alone encourage, in their own households?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The BBC, as the rest of the nation, is aware of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">influences</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> which would destroy society.  It has the right and responsibility to safeguard without being accused of being totalitarian and must stand up for itself over enforcing limits which protect all that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">this country has stood up for in the past in common decency and common sense</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We wish the BBC well and are sure that many would be reassured were the meretricious</span><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to disappear along with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the portrayal of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">extremes of evil.  The world and this country are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> moving into a very challenging time.  People need to be helped to be serious and responsible at the expense of sensationalism.  The BBC's great value and past international reputation needs the Trust's help for this to be continued and, where damaged, res</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tored. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Ann Whitaker</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Hon. Secretary</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0